            <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="true">
              <locus from="39"/>
              <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/20" type="supplied">The Proverbs of Solomon, according to the Peshitta version</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">
                <fw type="header">ܚܟܡܬܐ</fw>
              </rubric>
              <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠܡܬ. ܚܟܡܬܐ. ܕܫܠܝܡܘܢ̇ ܒܪ  ܕܘܝܕ<locus from="39a" to="39a"/>
              </finalRubric>
              <note>The missing portions are: ch. i. 1—v. 9 and ch. xii. 13—xiii. 4.</note>
              <note>Of the lessons, some are rubricated in the text, whilst others have been noted on the margins by a later hand.</note>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 10 1/8 in. by 7 3/4, consisting of 39 leaves, two of which, fol. 3 and 4, are slightly stained and torn. The quires, six in number, seem to have been originally signed with letters (see fol. 26). Several leaves are wanting at the beginning, and one leaf after fol. 10. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 19 to 22 lines. </p>
